queueReceiveData

public IAeWebServiceResponse queueReceiveData(IAeMessageContext aContext,
                                              org.w3c.dom.Document[] aDocArray)
                                       throws java.rmi.RemoteException,
                                              AeRequestException
Description copied from interface: IAeMessageQueue
Specialized version of queueReceiveData that accepts xml documents in lieu of our message container. The context must specify the full routing information of process qname and partner link OR specify only the service name. In either case, the missing information will be determined by introspecting the wsdl and matching the data to an operation.

Specified by:
queueReceiveData in interface IAeMessageQueue
Parameters:
aContext - must contain the process qname & partner link OR the service name, never both
aDocArray - array of xml documents that make up the message parts for the operaiton invoked
Throws:
java.rmi.RemoteException
AeRequestException
See Also:
IAeMessageQueue.queueReceiveData(org.activebpel.wsio.receive.IAeMessageContext, org.w3c.dom.Document[])
